After all the chaos of Black Friday, Small Business Saturday, and Cyber Monday - why not take some time and give back? Celebrate Giving Tuesday today.

Every year, Girl Scouts of Central California South provides financial scholarships for 5,000 girls. Without these scholarships, these girls would not be able to be Girl Scouts, depriving them of activities, events, and leaders that help them grow into girls of courage, confidence, and character. This #GivingTuesday, keep in mind just $20 will give a girl another year of the Girl Scouts Experience. Donate today: girlscoutsccs.org/donate.

Feedback on New York LIfe's website - we have 4 life insurance policies through them - tried to change the bank account info for payment:

1.  Very Antiquated System! Have to download and manually fill out forms and mail or fax them back!  Not the 1990's anymore lol.
2.  Very hard to navigate and find what you need.
3.  The link to download the form to change payment was broken, so I elected to contact my representative.
4.  The link to connect to him was broken.  I had to do a google search to even find his information.  
5.  No problems whatsoever with their service until you need to make changes.  A company this large should keep up with the times and make sure their website is updated and maintained.

According to the America After 3PM survey, more than 16% New Jersey children participate in an after-school program, up from 12 percent in 2004. But the unmet demand for afterschool — parents who would enroll their child in a program, if one were available — increased to over 36% in 2014. Demand is especially high among low-income, African-American and Hispanic families in urban centers like Newark.
